commit_message:
Use a custom yaml Loader and Dumper

During yaml transformations cfn_flip converts dicts to OrderedDict which
could conflict with other uses of yaml in a program. This change implements
a custom yaml loader and dumper to isolate the OrderedDict conversion to
just the cfn_flip transformations.

author: Gabriel Gironda
commit_message:
Fix conversion of dotted GetAtt attributes from YAML to JSON

Fn::GetAtt only supports two arguments in JSON, cf.

http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/intrinsic-function-reference-getatt.html

Some resource types have dotted attributes available, e.g. Endpoint.Address on
AWS::RDS::DBInstance. The existing functionality was causing output such as:

    "Fn::GetAtt": [
        "SentryRDSInstance",
        "Endpoint",
        "Port"
    ]

This fails CloudFormation validation.

author: Chris Deigan
commit_message:
Separate read/write steps of cfn-flip

Fixes https://github.com/awslabs/aws-cfn-template-flip/issues/91

The current process can lead to losing your template when specifying the
same input and output file, due to the write action interfering with the
read action.

This change performs the flip function, storing the result in memory,
then writing it. This allows users to use the same file as an
inputand output.
